720616f.title: Manhattan: Irving Place - 14th Street (East)
720616f.text:
Irving Place, east side, north from but not including.East 14th . Street, showing the executive offices of the Consolidated Gas Company (originally Manhattan Gas Company) at 4 Irving Place on the S.E. corner of 15th Street, and the cleaning from 16th to 17th Streets where the Washington Irving High School for Girls is about to be built, replacing old 3o-50 Irving Place. The Consolidated Gas Company building shown here was built before 18u7. Before 1916 it will be supersedec by a 20rstory builoing on this site, About the same time 30-24 Irving Place, the house shown here at and adioining the S.W. corner of 16th Street, will be replaced by a
13-story loft building.
On the S.E. corner of 18th Street may be seen the Huyler Chocolate
and Cocoa Factory.
March, 1909.
Brown Brothers.

720618f-a.title: Manhattan: Irving Place - 14th Street (East)
720618f-a.text:
Irving Place, south from East 15th to 14th (where it terminates) Streets, showing prominently the City TTheatre, which is on the south side, of East
14th Street, between Third and Fourth Aves.
September 2, 1936.
W.P.A. Photo.
Federal Art Project.

720619f-a.title: Manhattan: Irving Place - 14th Street (East)
720619f-a.text:
Irving Place, south from East 18th to 14th Streets. Towered building shown, is the Consolidated Gas Co. Building, and is located at the N.E. corner of 14th Street.
October 2, 1936.
P. L. Sperr.

720625f-a.title: Manhattan: Irving Place - 14th Street (East)
720625f-a.text:
Irving Place, east side, south from East 16th to East 14th Streets, showing W.P.A. employees engaged in street improvements. Note on the right, the City Theatre, located on the south side of East 14th Street, between Third and Fourth Aves. Shown in the center of the view are the lower
stories of the Consolidated Edison Co. Building.
September 2, 1936.
W.P.A. Photo.
Federal Art Project.
